This paper is primarily focused on the impact of neural network architecture on the efficiency of training, which is a core topic in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization algorithm used in neural network training, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of neural network architecture on computer vision tasks, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as a possible sub-category. The use of batch normalization and skip connections, which are common techniques in deep learning, suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of neural network architecture on the training dynamics, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
